                                                  written lines: 25 33; Uniform layout. The first part of the manuscript (folios 1-156) written in one column, with mostly 31 line a page. The second part has 2 columns a page, with 25 to 33 lines a column.Hair-side and flesh-side of the folios distinguishable.Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.Many passages marked off. Many marginal notes, some in Italian (see folio 48v, 49r). Part of folio 273r, and folios 273r-277v left blank. Parts of folio 157r, 258v omitted by the scribe.
